Kiribati is one of the countries that signed the agreement. The Paris Agreement is a legally binding agreement that aims to limit global warming to well below 2°C above pre-industrial levels and to pursue efforts to limit the temperature increase to 1.5°C above pre-industrial levels. The Paris Agreement also aims to strengthen the ability of countries to deal with the impacts of climate change. The Paris Agreement is a significant event for Kiribati because it is a commitment by the international community to address climate change.
